1
00:03:00,375 --> 00:03:02,002
Dad...

2
00:05:30,930 --> 00:05:35,518
Clear the ramp! 30 seconds! God be with you!

3
00:05:35,602 --> 00:05:37,770
Port side, stick. Starboard side, stick.

4
00:05:37,854 --> 00:05:40,190
Move fast and clear those mortar holes.

5
00:05:40,273 --> 00:05:43,026
l want to see plenty of beach between men.

6
00:05:43,109 --> 00:05:46,988
Five men is an opportunity. One is a waste of ammo.

7
00:05:47,071 --> 00:05:49,365
Keep the sand out of your weapons.

8
00:05:49,449 --> 00:05:51,201
Keep those actions clear.

9
00:05:51,284 --> 00:05:53,328
l'll see you on the beach.

10
00:06:25,985 --> 00:06:28,404
Open mortar holes!

11
00:06:44,379 --> 00:06:46,130
Over the side!

12
00:06:52,554 --> 00:06:54,722
Port and starboard, over...

13
00:08:03,833 --> 00:08:05,501
Jesus.

14
00:08:05,585 --> 00:08:06,920
Thank you...

15
00:10:26,392 --> 00:10:29,687
l said, what the hell do we do now, sir?

16
00:10:31,231 --> 00:10:32,232
Captain Miller!

17
00:10:33,316 --> 00:10:34,317
Captain Miller!

18
00:10:35,610 --> 00:10:37,320
Captain Miller!

19
00:10:37,403 --> 00:10:40,240
Sergeant Horvath!

20
00:10:40,323 --> 00:10:42,492
Move your men off the beach!

21
00:10:42,575 --> 00:10:44,202
Go!

22
00:10:44,285 --> 00:10:46,246
OK, you guys!

23
00:10:46,329 --> 00:10:49,290
Get on my ass! Follow me!

24
00:10:49,374 --> 00:10:51,125
What's the rallying point?

25
00:10:51,209 --> 00:10:53,253
Anywhere but here!

26
00:11:05,682 --> 00:11:07,225
The sea wall!

27
00:11:07,308 --> 00:11:08,852
Move up to the sea wall!

28
00:11:08,935 --> 00:11:10,728
Sir, l'm staying!

29
00:11:10,812 --> 00:11:13,898
Clear this beach! Make way for the others!

30
00:11:13,982 --> 00:11:16,276
This is all we got!

31
00:11:16,359 --> 00:11:20,363
Every inch of this beach has been pre-sighted!

32
00:11:20,446 --> 00:11:24,033
You stay here, you're dead men!

33
00:11:37,338 --> 00:11:38,965
Mama!

34
00:11:39,507 --> 00:11:40,675
Mama!

35
00:11:45,388 --> 00:11:47,974
Stay down! Stay down!

36
00:11:52,604 --> 00:11:54,147
What are you guys?

37
00:11:54,230 --> 00:11:57,192
104th Medical Battalion, sir!

38
00:11:57,275 --> 00:11:59,736
Here to set up field operations!

39
00:11:59,819 --> 00:12:01,654
Get rid of that crap!

40
00:12:01,738 --> 00:12:04,991
Grab yourselves some weapons. Follow me.

41
00:12:11,581 --> 00:12:13,249
l'm hit!

42
00:12:13,333 --> 00:12:14,500
Briggs!

43
00:12:19,631 --> 00:12:20,882
Get me out!

44
00:12:20,965 --> 00:12:23,593
l'm hit low. God!

45
00:12:23,676 --> 00:12:25,178
Medic!

46
00:12:25,261 --> 00:12:27,222
Navy Beach Battalion, sir.

47
00:12:27,305 --> 00:12:30,141
l gotta clear these obstacles for the tanks.

48
00:12:30,225 --> 00:12:32,685
All the armour's foundering in the Channel.

49
00:12:32,769 --> 00:12:34,020
Orders, sir.

50
00:12:34,103 --> 00:12:36,731
You go somewhere else. l'm clearing this one!

51
00:12:36,814 --> 00:12:37,982
Come on, Briggs!

52
00:12:43,238 --> 00:12:44,322
Medic!

53
00:13:21,192 --> 00:13:22,902
Move! Move!

54
00:13:29,993 --> 00:13:33,037
Move! Come on!

55
00:13:33,121 --> 00:13:34,497
Move!

56
00:13:54,893 --> 00:13:56,978
Shore party.

57
00:13:57,061 --> 00:13:58,980
No armour has made it ashore.

58
00:13:59,063 --> 00:14:01,149
We got no DD tanks.

59
00:14:01,232 --> 00:14:04,235
Dog One is not open.

60
00:14:04,319 --> 00:14:06,779
Who's in command here?

61
00:14:06,863 --> 00:14:08,865
You are, sir!

62
00:14:09,699 --> 00:14:11,701
- Sergeant Horvath! - Sir!

63
00:14:11,784 --> 00:14:13,995
You recognise where we are?

64
00:14:14,078 --> 00:14:17,498
Right where we're supposed to be, but no one else is!

65
00:14:17,582 --> 00:14:20,168
Nobody's where they're supposed to be.

66
00:14:20,251 --> 00:14:21,920
Shore party.

67
00:14:22,962 --> 00:14:24,589
First wave, ineffective.

68
00:14:24,672 --> 00:14:30,094
We do not hold the beach. Say again, we do not hold the beach.

69
00:14:30,178 --> 00:14:33,348
Sir, we got the leftovers from Fox Company,

70
00:14:33,431 --> 00:14:35,308
Able Company and George Company!

71
00:14:35,391 --> 00:14:39,604
Plus we got some Navy Demo guys and a Beachmaster!

72
00:14:39,687 --> 00:14:41,231
Shore party.

73
00:14:42,190 --> 00:14:43,650
Shore party.

74
00:14:48,780 --> 00:14:52,116
Cat-F, Cat-F, C...

75
00:14:55,203 --> 00:14:57,622
- Reiben here, sir! - Anybody else?

76
00:14:57,705 --> 00:14:59,290
Jackson, but that's about it.

77
00:14:59,374 --> 00:15:01,626
Mellish here.

78
00:15:01,709 --> 00:15:03,836
Caparzo! DeForest's back with Wade.

79
00:15:03,920 --> 00:15:07,215
He's hurt so bad he says he sprung 100 leaks.

80
00:15:07,298 --> 00:15:09,425
Wade says he's all used up.

81
00:15:09,509 --> 00:15:11,219
Find somebody you can help.

82
00:15:11,302 --> 00:15:14,639
He's battalion surgeon, sir!

83
00:15:18,351 --> 00:15:19,435
Get his attention.

84
00:15:19,519 --> 00:15:20,520
Wade!

85
00:15:20,603 --> 00:15:21,563
Yo, doc!

86
00:15:21,646 --> 00:15:24,023
Wade!

87
00:15:31,114 --> 00:15:33,032
Get him off the beach.

88
00:15:33,116 --> 00:15:35,326
l got it! We stopped the bleeding!

89
00:15:35,410 --> 00:15:37,954
We stopped the bleeding!

90
00:15:38,037 --> 00:15:39,497
Fuck!

91
00:15:39,581 --> 00:15:43,418
Just give us a fucking chance, you son of a bitch!

92
00:15:43,501 --> 00:15:45,461
Son of a fucking cocksucker!

93
00:15:45,545 --> 00:15:48,047
Come on, Wade! lt's Mellish!

94
00:15:48,131 --> 00:15:49,924
Wade!

95
00:15:51,384 --> 00:15:54,846
We found Miller! Let's move! Let's move!

96
00:15:54,929 --> 00:15:57,974
Oh, God. Oh, God.

97
00:16:02,187 --> 00:16:05,148
This is all? This is all that's made it?

98
00:16:05,231 --> 00:16:06,983
We got scattered pretty bad, sir.

99
00:16:07,066 --> 00:16:08,943
There's bound to be more.

100
00:16:09,027 --> 00:16:11,654
Not enough. This is not enough.

101
00:16:11,738 --> 00:16:12,947
Dog One exit...

102
00:16:13,031 --> 00:16:15,408
On the right. Or is it left? Shit!

103
00:16:15,491 --> 00:16:19,287
No, Vierville is west of us. This is Dog One.

104
00:16:19,370 --> 00:16:20,788
They're killing us!

105
00:16:20,872 --> 00:16:24,167
We don't have a fucking chance, and that ain't fair!

106
00:16:24,250 --> 00:16:26,502
Gather weapons and ammo!

107
00:16:27,045 --> 00:16:29,214
Gather weapons and ammo!

108
00:16:29,297 --> 00:16:32,383
Come on, drag 'em in off the sand!

109
00:16:41,059 --> 00:16:42,810
Hey, Reiben, Reiben, Reiben,

110
00:16:42,894 --> 00:16:44,395
where's your BAR?

111
00:16:44,479 --> 00:16:47,273
Bottom of the channel, sir. Nearly drowned me.

112
00:16:47,357 --> 00:16:49,317
Find a replacement.

113
00:16:51,277 --> 00:16:54,239
Bangalores! Bring up some bangalores!

114
00:16:54,322 --> 00:16:57,492
Grenades, grenades!

115
00:16:57,575 --> 00:16:59,244
Get 'em over here!

116
00:17:01,871 --> 00:17:03,706
Bangalores up the line!

117
00:17:03,790 --> 00:17:05,875
Bangalores up the line!

118
00:17:05,959 --> 00:17:08,253
Heads up! Bangers coming your way!

119
00:17:08,336 --> 00:17:10,547
Come on, come on, come on!

120
00:17:10,630 --> 00:17:11,714
Jackson here, sir!

121
00:17:11,798 --> 00:17:13,007
Reiben back, sir!

122
00:17:20,390 --> 00:17:22,976
One more. Give me one more.

123
00:17:26,521 --> 00:17:29,190
Oh, my God, it hurts!

124
00:17:29,274 --> 00:17:30,608
l'm gonna die!

125
00:17:30,692 --> 00:17:33,111
Oh, my God! Oh, Jesus!

126
00:17:33,194 --> 00:17:34,320
Oh, my God!

127
00:17:35,572 --> 00:17:37,407
Keep it moving. Keep it moving.

128
00:17:37,490 --> 00:17:39,200
Almost got it.

129
00:17:39,284 --> 00:17:40,285
Jesus!

130
00:17:40,368 --> 00:17:43,121
Lucky bastard.

131
00:17:43,204 --> 00:17:45,498
Keep it moving. You got it?

132
00:17:45,582 --> 00:17:49,168
God! God, help me!

133
00:17:49,252 --> 00:17:51,588
You're not gonna die.

134
00:17:51,671 --> 00:17:54,424
You're fine. Don't look at it.

135
00:17:54,507 --> 00:17:58,261
Bangalores! Clear the shingle!

136
00:17:58,344 --> 00:18:02,557
Fire in the hole! Fire in the hole!

137
00:18:15,778 --> 00:18:18,239
We're in business! Defilade!

138
00:18:18,323 --> 00:18:20,241
Other side of the hole!

139
00:18:32,962 --> 00:18:34,923
That's it! Let's go!

140
00:18:38,218 --> 00:18:40,428
lnspected. Morphine.

141
00:18:43,556 --> 00:18:45,391
Routine.

142
00:18:50,313 --> 00:18:52,273
Priority.

143
00:18:55,944 --> 00:18:56,945
He's gone.

144
00:19:10,208 --> 00:19:12,210
Son of a...

145
00:19:12,293 --> 00:19:14,379
Get in there.

146
00:19:14,462 --> 00:19:15,838
Fuck. l can't move.

147
00:19:15,922 --> 00:19:17,966
Mellish, give me your bayonet.

148
00:19:38,194 --> 00:19:40,446
Two MG-42s and two mortars.

149
00:19:40,530 --> 00:19:42,657
Add 20, left 30.

150
00:19:45,368 --> 00:19:46,953
There's a little defilade,

151
00:19:47,036 --> 00:19:50,290
but it's the perfect position if we get some armour.

152
00:19:50,373 --> 00:19:53,251
We gotta open up this draw! Get this draw open.

153
00:19:53,334 --> 00:19:55,336
Reiben, Mellish, let's get into the war!

154
00:19:55,420 --> 00:19:58,506
Grab some cover and put some fire on that crew.

155
00:19:58,590 --> 00:20:02,552
Davis, DeBernardo, Young, Valk, get ready.

156
00:20:04,179 --> 00:20:06,055
Covering fire!

157
00:20:09,851 --> 00:20:11,936
Go, go, go!

158
00:20:25,241 --> 00:20:27,118
Goddamn firing squad.

159
00:20:27,202 --> 00:20:30,455
lt's the only way we can get everybody out.

160
00:20:30,538 --> 00:20:32,999
Short, Payton, McDonald, Parkes!

161
00:20:33,082 --> 00:20:34,918
You're next!

162
00:20:35,001 --> 00:20:39,380
- Why not hand out blindfolds? - All we'll do here is die.

163
00:20:39,464 --> 00:20:41,299
Covering fire!

164
00:20:43,092 --> 00:20:45,720
Go, go, go!

165
00:20:45,803 --> 00:20:46,804
Come on!

166
00:20:46,888 --> 00:20:48,723
Come on! Come on!

167
00:20:48,806 --> 00:20:50,225
Go, Goddamit!

168
00:21:02,654 --> 00:21:04,155
Jackson.

169
00:21:04,239 --> 00:21:05,240
Sir.

170
00:21:05,323 --> 00:21:06,950
See that impact crater?

171
00:21:07,033 --> 00:21:08,159
Yes, sir.

172
00:21:08,243 --> 00:21:12,372
That should give complete defilade from that machine gun.

173
00:21:12,455 --> 00:21:14,707
Wait for my command.

174
00:21:20,046 --> 00:21:21,047
Go!

175
00:21:32,100 --> 00:21:35,728
Captain, if your mother saw that, she'd be very upset.

176
00:21:35,812 --> 00:21:38,439
l thought you were my mother.

177
00:21:38,982 --> 00:21:41,985
Be not thou far from me, O Lord.

178
00:21:46,447 --> 00:21:49,450
My God, l am sorry for offending Thee.

179
00:21:51,828 --> 00:21:55,373
l detest my sins for having offended Thee, O Lord.

180
00:21:55,456 --> 00:21:56,583
Listen to me, Lord.

181
00:22:02,755 --> 00:22:04,757
All my strength...

182
00:22:04,841 --> 00:22:06,718
haste Thee to help me.

183
00:22:22,150 --> 00:22:25,570
Dog One exit! Right here!

184
00:22:25,653 --> 00:22:27,363
We're in business!

185
00:22:28,573 --> 00:22:30,617
Move! Move!

186
00:23:11,783 --> 00:23:12,742
Reiben.

187
00:23:12,825 --> 00:23:15,286
- Let's go, sarge. Go! - Reiben.

188
00:23:43,439 --> 00:23:44,983
Come on, Doyle!

189
00:23:46,860 --> 00:23:48,027
Sarge.

190
00:23:53,283 --> 00:23:54,701
Flame!

191
00:23:54,784 --> 00:23:56,578
Doyle, do it!

192
00:24:01,374 --> 00:24:03,918
Don't shoot! Let 'em burn!

193
00:24:25,857 --> 00:24:28,193
''Comrade?'' You son of a bitch!

194
00:24:29,235 --> 00:24:31,237
Lie down!

195
00:24:59,265 --> 00:25:01,726
Cease fire! Cease fire!

196
00:25:01,809 --> 00:25:02,769
Cut it out!

197
00:25:02,852 --> 00:25:05,355
Cut it out! Cease fire!

198
00:25:05,438 --> 00:25:07,941
Sugar Cane. Sugar Charlie Three.

199
00:25:08,024 --> 00:25:11,110
Say again, Dog One is open. Send in the dozers.

200
00:25:11,194 --> 00:25:14,781
l'm waiting to tie in my flanks. Over.

201
00:25:14,864 --> 00:25:16,407
What?

202
00:25:19,327 --> 00:25:22,789
What? l'm sorry, l can't understand you.

203
00:25:30,255 --> 00:25:33,174
What'd he say? What'd he say?

204
00:25:33,258 --> 00:25:36,177
''Look, l washed for supper.''

205
00:25:48,898 --> 00:25:51,025
- Hey, Fish. - Yeah?

206
00:25:51,109 --> 00:25:54,737
Look at this. A Hitler Youth knife.

207
00:25:54,821 --> 00:25:57,198
Now it's a Shabbat challah cutter, right?

208
00:26:07,375 --> 00:26:09,002
Keep it moving!

209
00:27:09,312 --> 00:27:11,356
That's quite a view.

210
00:27:12,649 --> 00:27:14,192
Yes, it is.

211
00:27:15,860 --> 00:27:17,695
Quite a view.

212
00:28:52,040 --> 00:28:54,167
''Dear Mr Brian Boyd,

213
00:28:54,250 --> 00:28:56,002
''no doubt you have received information...''

214
00:28:56,085 --> 00:28:57,295
''Dear Mrs Jensen...''

215
00:28:57,378 --> 00:28:58,963
''..the death of your son.''

216
00:28:59,047 --> 00:29:00,757
''..no words can relieve the grief...''

217
00:29:00,840 --> 00:29:03,134
''We have felt his loss tremendously.''

218
00:29:03,218 --> 00:29:06,179
''He was a fine soldier...''

219
00:29:06,262 --> 00:29:07,889
''We were involved

220
00:29:07,972 --> 00:29:11,142
''in one of the most important operations of this war.''

221
00:29:11,226 --> 00:29:13,186
''Al held us all together.

222
00:29:13,269 --> 00:29:14,979
''He was always first to volunteer...''

223
00:29:15,063 --> 00:29:16,773
''..came to a clearing

224
00:29:16,856 --> 00:29:18,525
''where 4,000 troops had passed.''

225
00:29:18,608 --> 00:29:21,110
''Your husband served in a unit

226
00:29:21,194 --> 00:29:23,738
''whose dangerous duty is to place itself beyond...''

227
00:29:23,821 --> 00:29:26,741
''..we all cherish and hold so dear.

228
00:29:26,824 --> 00:29:30,745
''The loss of Lee and others like him is a distinct blow.''

229
00:29:30,828 --> 00:29:32,914
''l understand your desire

230
00:29:32,997 --> 00:29:36,751
''to learn about circumstances leading to his death.''

231
00:30:28,636 --> 00:30:32,098
Colonel, l've got something you should know about.

232
00:30:33,850 --> 00:30:37,187
These two men died in Normandy.

233
00:30:37,270 --> 00:30:39,189
This one at Omaha beach.

234
00:30:40,231 --> 00:30:41,649
Sean Ryan.

235
00:30:41,733 --> 00:30:43,985
This man at Utah.

236
00:30:45,236 --> 00:30:46,821
Peter Ryan.

237
00:30:50,617 --> 00:30:53,786
This man was killed last week in New Guinea.

238
00:30:56,456 --> 00:30:57,957
Daniel...

239
00:30:58,041 --> 00:30:59,334
Ryan.

240
00:30:59,417 --> 00:31:01,211
The three are brothers, sir.

241
00:31:01,294 --> 00:31:03,213
l've just learned that this afternoon

242
00:31:03,296 --> 00:31:05,757
their mother will get all three telegrams.

243
00:31:10,053 --> 00:31:12,347
That's not all. There's a fourth brother.

244
00:31:12,430 --> 00:31:16,184
He parachuted in the night before the invasion.

245
00:31:16,267 --> 00:31:18,144
He's somewhere in Normandy.

246
00:31:18,228 --> 00:31:21,523
- ls he alive? - We don't know.

247
00:31:24,275 --> 00:31:25,527
Come with me.

248
00:33:10,465 --> 00:33:13,009
'Goddamit.'

249
00:33:13,092 --> 00:33:17,388
All four were in the 29th Division, but we split them up

250
00:33:17,472 --> 00:33:20,433
after the Sullivan brothers died on the Juneau.

251
00:33:20,517 --> 00:33:22,727
Any contact with the fourth son, James?

252
00:33:22,810 --> 00:33:27,148
No, sir. He was dropped about 15 miles inland near Neuville.

253
00:33:27,232 --> 00:33:29,150
That's still deep behind German lines.

254
00:33:29,234 --> 00:33:33,154
There's no way to know where the hell he was dropped.

255
00:33:33,238 --> 00:33:37,742
First reports out of SHAEF said the 101st is scattered to hell.

256
00:33:37,825 --> 00:33:39,786
There's misdrops all over Normandy.

257
00:33:39,869 --> 00:33:43,498
Assuming Ryan survived the jump, he could be anywhere.

258
00:33:43,581 --> 00:33:46,125
ln fact, he's probably KlA.

259
00:33:46,209 --> 00:33:50,129
And frankly, sir, we go sending some sort of rescue mission,

260
00:33:50,213 --> 00:33:53,007
flat-hatting through swarms of German reinforcements

261
00:33:53,091 --> 00:33:54,759
along our axis of advance,

262
00:33:54,843 --> 00:33:56,636
they're gonna be KlA, too.

263
00:34:19,826 --> 00:34:21,786
l have a letter here...

264
00:34:23,037 --> 00:34:27,166
written a long time ago to a Mrs Bixby in Boston.

265
00:34:27,250 --> 00:34:29,377
So bear with me.

266
00:34:31,963 --> 00:34:33,423
''Dear Madam,

267
00:34:33,506 --> 00:34:37,427
''l have been shown in the files of the War Department

268
00:34:37,510 --> 00:34:40,805
''a statement of the Adjutant General of Massachusetts

269
00:34:40,889 --> 00:34:44,184
''that you are the mother of five...

270
00:34:46,227 --> 00:34:49,814
''sons who died gloriously on the field of battle.

271
00:34:52,901 --> 00:34:57,947
''l feel how weak and fruitless must be any words of mine

272
00:34:58,031 --> 00:35:01,075
''that would attempt to beguile you from the grief

273
00:35:01,159 --> 00:35:05,163
''of a loss so overwhelming.

274
00:35:05,246 --> 00:35:07,749
''But l cannot refrain from tendering to you

275
00:35:07,832 --> 00:35:11,169
''the consolation that may be found

276
00:35:11,252 --> 00:35:15,798
''in the thanks of the republic they died to save.

277
00:35:19,093 --> 00:35:21,137
''l pray that Our Heavenly Father

278
00:35:21,221 --> 00:35:24,140
''may assuage the anguish of your bereavement

279
00:35:24,224 --> 00:35:28,603
''and leave only the cherished memory of the loved lost...

280
00:35:28,686 --> 00:35:31,356
''and the solemn pride that must be yours

281
00:35:31,439 --> 00:35:33,775
''to have laid so costly a sacrifice

282
00:35:33,858 --> 00:35:35,735
''upon the altar of freedom.

283
00:35:35,818 --> 00:35:39,197
''Yours very sincerely and respectfully...

284
00:35:39,280 --> 00:35:40,698
''Abraham Lincoln.''

285
00:36:00,260 --> 00:36:02,971
That boy is alive.

286
00:36:03,054 --> 00:36:05,932
We are gonna send somebody to find him...

287
00:36:06,850 --> 00:36:10,728
and we are gonna get him the hell out of there.

288
00:36:10,812 --> 00:36:11,813
Yes, sir.

289
00:36:24,742 --> 00:36:27,620
We expected 32 tanks, 27 didn't make it.

290
00:36:27,704 --> 00:36:31,082
- Miller, Charlie Company. - Go in, Captain.

291
00:36:31,165 --> 00:36:34,377
lf we don't off-load those Shermans by 0600,

292
00:36:34,460 --> 00:36:37,088
we'll have an entire division stuck at Carentan

293
00:36:37,172 --> 00:36:39,132
with its pants around its ankles.

294
00:36:39,215 --> 00:36:41,176
Well, you let me know.

295
00:36:41,259 --> 00:36:44,929
Have Charlie Company hold Vierville until we get there.

296
00:36:45,013 --> 00:36:47,223
Yes, sir. Runner!

297
00:36:52,478 --> 00:36:56,065
Airborne was supposed to win an open door for us.

298
00:36:56,149 --> 00:36:58,985
They misdropped, scattered everything into the wind.

299
00:36:59,068 --> 00:37:00,153
What's your situation?

300
00:37:00,236 --> 00:37:02,739
Yes, sir. Sector four is secure.

301
00:37:04,866 --> 00:37:07,076
We took out towed 88s

302
00:37:07,160 --> 00:37:09,913
here, here...and here.

303
00:37:09,996 --> 00:37:11,664
They'd already gotten four Shermans

304
00:37:11,748 --> 00:37:13,750
and some deuce-and-a-halves.

305
00:37:13,833 --> 00:37:16,169
These two minefields are one big one.

306
00:37:16,252 --> 00:37:17,670
We tried going through,

307
00:37:17,754 --> 00:37:20,757
but it turned into a high-density field...

308
00:37:20,840 --> 00:37:22,175
little bit of everything.

309
00:37:22,258 --> 00:37:24,969
Spreng mine 44s, pot mines, A-200s...

310
00:37:25,053 --> 00:37:29,182
the wooden bastards that the mine detectors don't pick up.

311
00:37:29,265 --> 00:37:33,144
This road here... they placed Teller mine 43s,

312
00:37:33,228 --> 00:37:34,979
l guess for our tanks...

313
00:37:35,063 --> 00:37:38,107
from here to the edge of the village.

314
00:37:38,191 --> 00:37:40,818
So we marked 'em, called the engineers.

315
00:37:40,902 --> 00:37:42,195
Resistance?

316
00:37:42,278 --> 00:37:44,155
We had higher support expectations, sir.

317
00:37:44,239 --> 00:37:46,783
There was an understrength company without artillery.

318
00:37:46,866 --> 00:37:50,036
Wehrmacht 346 lnfantry, von Luck Kampfgruppe.

319
00:37:50,119 --> 00:37:52,163
We ended up with 23 prisoners.

320
00:37:52,247 --> 00:37:54,415
We turned them over to MPs.

321
00:37:58,253 --> 00:38:00,213
What about our casualties?

322
00:38:01,256 --> 00:38:02,423
Well...

323
00:38:02,507 --> 00:38:04,175
the figures...

324
00:38:04,259 --> 00:38:06,761
were 35 dead...

325
00:38:06,845 --> 00:38:08,137
times two wounded.

326
00:38:08,221 --> 00:38:13,184
They just... didn't wanna give up those 88s.

327
00:38:13,268 --> 00:38:16,145
lt was tough, that's why you got it.

328
00:38:16,229 --> 00:38:17,772
Yes, sir.

329
00:38:19,023 --> 00:38:20,149
John...

330
00:38:23,152 --> 00:38:25,405
l've got another one for you.

331
00:38:25,488 --> 00:38:28,575
- Yes, sir. - Straight from the top.

332
00:38:34,873 --> 00:38:39,169
We're taking a squad to Neuville on a public relations mission.

333
00:38:39,252 --> 00:38:41,212
You leading a squad?

334
00:38:41,296 --> 00:38:46,176
Some Private lost three brothers and got a ticket home.

335
00:38:46,259 --> 00:38:47,552
How come Neuville?

336
00:38:47,635 --> 00:38:51,181
They think he's part of all those airborne misdrops.

337
00:38:51,264 --> 00:38:55,059
lt won't be easy finding one particular soldier.

338
00:38:55,143 --> 00:38:57,812
Like finding a needle in a stack of needles.

339
00:38:57,896 --> 00:38:59,355
What about the company?

340
00:38:59,439 --> 00:39:03,151
We take our pick, the rest get folded into Baker.

341
00:39:03,234 --> 00:39:04,819
Jesus Christ.

342
00:39:04,903 --> 00:39:07,197
They took away your company?

343
00:39:07,280 --> 00:39:11,409
lt wasn't my company. lt was the army's. So they told me.

344
00:39:11,492 --> 00:39:15,163
Give me Reiben on BAR, Jackson, Wade, Beasley and Caparzo.

345
00:39:15,246 --> 00:39:16,956
Beasley's dead.

346
00:39:17,040 --> 00:39:20,251
All right, Mellish, then. We got anybody speaks French?

347
00:39:20,335 --> 00:39:22,795
Not that l know of.

348
00:39:22,879 --> 00:39:24,130
What about Talbot?

349
00:39:24,214 --> 00:39:26,549
- This morning. - Oh. All right.

350
00:39:26,633 --> 00:39:29,177
l'll try to dig up another interpreter.

351
00:39:29,260 --> 00:39:31,346
Assemble at battalion motor pool.

352
00:39:31,429 --> 00:39:32,388
Yes, sir.

353
00:39:32,472 --> 00:39:34,766
- What we doing? - Listen up... What?

354
00:39:34,849 --> 00:39:36,142
What we gonna do?

355
00:39:36,226 --> 00:39:39,979
You're going home with a hunk of cheese in your ass, Caparzo.

356
00:39:40,063 --> 00:39:42,815
You like it in the ass.

357
00:39:42,899 --> 00:39:44,776
Attention!

358
00:39:44,859 --> 00:39:46,194
As you were.

359
00:39:46,277 --> 00:39:47,987
l'm looking for Corporal Upham,

360
00:39:48,071 --> 00:39:50,240
- Timothy E. - l'm Upham, sir.

361
00:39:50,323 --> 00:39:52,909
- You speak French and German? - Yes, sir.

362
00:39:52,992 --> 00:39:53,952
Accent?

363
00:39:54,035 --> 00:39:56,913
A slight one in French. My German's clean, sir.

364
00:39:56,996 --> 00:39:59,582
You're reassigned to me. Grab your gear.

365
00:39:59,666 --> 00:40:02,544
We're going to Neuville. When was this updated?

366
00:40:02,627 --> 00:40:04,462
As of 0830, sir.

367
00:40:04,546 --> 00:40:06,005
Uh, sir...

368
00:40:06,089 --> 00:40:07,757
These two axes advance south...

369
00:40:07,841 --> 00:40:09,759
Sir, there are Germans in Neuville.

370
00:40:09,843 --> 00:40:15,348
- Yes, Corporal. - Sir, a LOT of Germans.

371
00:40:15,431 --> 00:40:16,933
You have a problem with that, Corporal?

372
00:40:17,016 --> 00:40:21,312
No, l've never been in combat. l make maps, translate...

373
00:40:21,396 --> 00:40:24,315
l need someone who speaks French and German.

374
00:40:24,399 --> 00:40:25,650
My guys were killed.

375
00:40:25,733 --> 00:40:28,653
But l haven't held a weapon since training, sir.

376
00:40:28,736 --> 00:40:32,073
- Did you fire the weapon? - Yes, sir.

377
00:40:32,156 --> 00:40:34,659
- Then get your gear. - Yes, sir.

378
00:40:36,369 --> 00:40:37,996
Sir, may l...

379
00:40:42,709 --> 00:40:45,086
May l bring my typewriter, sir?

380
00:40:49,465 --> 00:40:50,508
Yes, sir.

381
00:40:54,179 --> 00:40:56,681
Thank you very much, sir.

382
00:40:56,764 --> 00:40:59,267
- That a souvenir? - No, sir.

383
00:40:59,350 --> 00:41:00,977
Take your time, Corporal.

384
00:41:04,480 --> 00:41:07,066
Look on the bright side, Corporal.

385
00:41:07,150 --> 00:41:08,318
Yes, sir.

386
00:41:08,401 --> 00:41:12,322
For one thing... you don't need to carry those.

387
00:41:12,405 --> 00:41:13,740
You'll need that.

388
00:41:13,823 --> 00:41:16,659
Need this. Yes, sir. Don't need that...

389
00:42:15,718 --> 00:42:17,595
You want your head blown off?

390
00:42:17,679 --> 00:42:20,640
Don't fuckin' touch me with those little rat claws.

391
00:42:20,723 --> 00:42:22,976
Get the fuck back in formation.

392
00:42:24,143 --> 00:42:26,855
l was wondering where you're from, that's...

393
00:42:32,110 --> 00:42:33,653
Caparzo, is it?

394
00:42:33,736 --> 00:42:35,238
Hey, drop dead, Corporal.

395
00:42:35,321 --> 00:42:36,447
Got you.

396
00:42:36,531 --> 00:42:41,035
And saluting the captain makes him a target for Germans.

397
00:42:41,119 --> 00:42:44,497
So don't do it, especially when l'm next to him.

398
00:42:46,708 --> 00:42:48,251
Corporal, what's your book about?

399
00:42:48,334 --> 00:42:50,879
- Watch your rifle. - Sorry.

400
00:42:50,962 --> 00:42:53,590
lt's supposed to be about the bonds of brotherhood

401
00:42:53,673 --> 00:42:55,633
that develop between soldiers during war.

402
00:42:55,717 --> 00:42:57,719
Brotherhood?

403
00:42:57,802 --> 00:42:59,596
What do you know about brotherhood?

404
00:42:59,679 --> 00:43:02,182
Get a load of this guy, Fish.

405
00:43:02,265 --> 00:43:04,517
Ask the captain where he's from.

406
00:43:04,601 --> 00:43:06,060
Yeah, ask the captain.

407
00:43:06,144 --> 00:43:08,146
He'll tell you everything you wanna know.

408
00:43:08,229 --> 00:43:11,024
You wanna explain the math of this to me?

409
00:43:11,107 --> 00:43:15,653
Why risk the lives of the eight of us to save one guy?

410
00:43:15,737 --> 00:43:18,406
20 degrees. Anybody wanna answer?

411
00:43:18,489 --> 00:43:22,160
Reiben, think about the poor bastard's mother.

412
00:43:22,243 --> 00:43:24,037
l got a mother, all right?

413
00:43:24,120 --> 00:43:26,623
l mean, you got a mother. Sarge has got a mother.

414
00:43:26,706 --> 00:43:29,918
Shit, l bet even the captain's got a mother.

415
00:43:30,001 --> 00:43:33,046
Well, not the captain, but the rest of us.

416
00:43:33,129 --> 00:43:36,549
''Theirs not to reason why, theirs but to do and die.''

417
00:43:39,093 --> 00:43:42,222
What does that mean? We're all supposed to die?

418
00:43:42,305 --> 00:43:45,225
Upham's talking about our duty as soldiers.

419
00:43:45,308 --> 00:43:46,601
Yes, sir.

420
00:43:46,684 --> 00:43:49,270
We have orders to follow. That supersedes everything,

421
00:43:49,354 --> 00:43:50,730
including your mothers.

422
00:43:50,813 --> 00:43:52,106
Thank you, sir.

423
00:43:52,190 --> 00:43:54,609
Even if you think the mission's fubar, sir?

424
00:43:54,692 --> 00:43:57,362
Especially if you think the mission's fubar.

425
00:43:57,445 --> 00:43:58,947
What's ''fubar''?

426
00:43:59,030 --> 00:44:01,741
Oh, it's German. Yeah.

427
00:44:01,824 --> 00:44:04,077
Never heard of that.

428
00:44:04,160 --> 00:44:05,620
Sir...

429
00:44:05,703 --> 00:44:07,997
l have an opinion on this matter.

430
00:44:08,081 --> 00:44:11,042
Well, by all means, share it with the squad.

431
00:44:11,125 --> 00:44:13,253
Well, from my way of thinking, sir,

432
00:44:13,336 --> 00:44:16,047
this entire mission is a serious misallocation

433
00:44:16,130 --> 00:44:18,049
of valuable military resources.

434
00:44:18,132 --> 00:44:19,843
Yeah. Go on.

435
00:44:19,926 --> 00:44:22,011
Well, it seems to me, sir,

436
00:44:22,095 --> 00:44:25,473
that God made me a fine instrument of warfare.

437
00:44:26,516 --> 00:44:29,602
Reiben, pay attention. This is the way to gripe!

438
00:44:29,686 --> 00:44:30,645
Continue, Jackson.

439
00:44:30,728 --> 00:44:32,021
What l mean, sir,

440
00:44:32,105 --> 00:44:37,151
if you put me and this rifle within one mile of Adolf Hitler

441
00:44:37,235 --> 00:44:39,654
with a clear line of sight, sir...

442
00:44:39,737 --> 00:44:43,116
Pack your bags, fellas. War's over. Amen.

443
00:44:43,199 --> 00:44:44,659
Oh, that's brilliant, bumpkin.

444
00:44:44,742 --> 00:44:48,037
So, Captain, what about you? You don't gripe at all?

445
00:44:48,121 --> 00:44:51,040
l don't gripe to you, Reiben. l'm a captain.

446
00:44:51,124 --> 00:44:54,294
There's a chain of command. Gripes go up, not down.

447
00:44:54,377 --> 00:44:59,132
You gripe to me, l gripe to my superiors and so on.

448
00:44:59,215 --> 00:45:03,094
l don't gripe to you or in front of you.

449
00:45:03,178 --> 00:45:05,054
l'm sorry, sir, but, uh...

450
00:45:05,138 --> 00:45:09,642
Let's say you weren't a captain. What would you say then?

451
00:45:09,726 --> 00:45:11,060
Well, in that case,

452
00:45:11,144 --> 00:45:14,022
l'd say this is an excellent mission, sir,

453
00:45:14,105 --> 00:45:16,024
with an extremely valuable objective, sir,

454
00:45:16,107 --> 00:45:18,651
worthy of my best efforts, sir.

455
00:45:18,735 --> 00:45:21,237
Moreover...l feel heartfelt sorrow

456
00:45:21,321 --> 00:45:24,032
for the mother of Private James Ryan

457
00:45:24,115 --> 00:45:28,411
and will lay down my life and the lives of my men,

458
00:45:28,494 --> 00:45:31,581
especially you, Reiben, to ease her suffering.

459
00:45:32,665 --> 00:45:35,168
- He's good. - l love him.

460
00:45:45,512 --> 00:45:46,638
Right.

461
00:46:28,513 --> 00:46:30,223
Thunder!

462
00:46:30,306 --> 00:46:31,641
Flash!

463
00:46:31,724 --> 00:46:33,017
Upham, over there.

464
00:46:33,101 --> 00:46:35,103
Reiben, you four go.

465
00:46:44,737 --> 00:46:46,364
Go, go, go, go, go.

466
00:46:51,744 --> 00:46:53,413
You're a welcome sight.

467
00:46:53,496 --> 00:46:54,998
Our relief showed up.

468
00:46:55,081 --> 00:46:56,624
How many are you?

469
00:46:56,708 --> 00:46:59,127
Just eight. We're not your relief. Sorry.

470
00:46:59,210 --> 00:47:01,004
What do you mean, sir?

471
00:47:01,087 --> 00:47:03,047
We're here for a Private Ryan.

472
00:47:03,131 --> 00:47:04,841
Who? Ryan? What for?

473
00:47:04,924 --> 00:47:07,343
- ls he here? - l don't know.

474
00:47:07,427 --> 00:47:13,391
Maybe on the other side of town. The Germans cut us in two.

475
00:47:13,474 --> 00:47:17,228
- What's his name again? - Ryan. James Ryan.

476
00:47:17,312 --> 00:47:18,646
He dropped in with 101st.

477
00:47:18,730 --> 00:47:21,441
- Goldman, get me a runner. - Runner!

478
00:47:21,524 --> 00:47:22,859
Come on.

479
00:47:27,113 --> 00:47:29,073
Jonesy, make a hole there!

480
00:47:30,575 --> 00:47:34,037
We got stopped by intense rifle action from the eastward.

481
00:47:34,120 --> 00:47:36,998
The Germans have been reinforcing regiments all day.

482
00:47:37,081 --> 00:47:39,501
lt's been quiet for about 45 minutes.

483
00:47:39,584 --> 00:47:43,004
Most of the German fire is concentrated to the westward.

484
00:47:43,087 --> 00:47:44,631
Who's on the loudspeaker?

485
00:47:44,714 --> 00:47:46,049
That's Dagwood DÃ¼sseldorf,

486
00:47:46,132 --> 00:47:48,801
our friendly neighbourhood morale officer.

487
00:47:48,885 --> 00:47:51,012
The Statue of Liberty is kaputt.

488
00:47:51,095 --> 00:47:54,641
''The Statue of Liberty is kaputt.''

489
00:47:54,724 --> 00:47:56,267
That's disconcerting.

490
00:47:59,521 --> 00:48:01,022
Take the second left...

491
00:48:01,105 --> 00:48:05,026
Your father was circumcised by my rabbi, you prick!

492
00:48:05,109 --> 00:48:08,029
Private Ryan, James, probably misdropped with 101 .

493
00:48:08,112 --> 00:48:10,031
- Got that? - Cover!

494
00:48:17,497 --> 00:48:18,873
Go!

495
00:48:42,522 --> 00:48:44,315
Those sadistic fuckin' animals!

496
00:48:44,399 --> 00:48:45,358
Get down.

497
00:48:45,441 --> 00:48:48,611
They know we're not in contact, they'll get the runners.

498
00:48:48,695 --> 00:48:50,196
Why keep shooting him?

499
00:48:50,280 --> 00:48:53,032
Long as he lives, he carries the message.

500
00:48:53,116 --> 00:48:55,618
- We'd do the same. - We wouldn't!

501
00:48:55,702 --> 00:48:59,289
- Get ready to travel. - Yes, sir.

502
00:48:59,372 --> 00:49:02,667
Try again to let Captain Hamill know we're coming.

503
00:49:02,750 --> 00:49:04,043
What's the rest of Neuville like?

504
00:49:04,127 --> 00:49:08,006
Uh, next block's got two-storey buildings both sides.

505
00:49:08,089 --> 00:49:11,384
A lotta windows and a square on the left.

506
00:49:11,467 --> 00:49:13,928
- Show me. - Sarge, hold right here.

507
00:49:14,012 --> 00:49:15,054
Yes, sir.

508
00:49:19,100 --> 00:49:22,604
Let's stay out of this enfilade and use the buildings.

509
00:49:22,687 --> 00:49:25,648
Try a left hook. Two of yours, two of mine.

510
00:49:25,732 --> 00:49:27,775
Hastings, Goldman, up front!

511
00:49:29,110 --> 00:49:30,445
Reiben, Caparzo.

512
00:49:30,528 --> 00:49:32,363
Fundamentals. Short runs.

513
00:49:32,447 --> 00:49:34,866
High and low at the corners.

514
00:49:34,949 --> 00:49:37,243
Be prepared for close contact.

515
00:49:37,327 --> 00:49:40,622
Go. Upham, stay with Sergeant Horvath.

516
00:49:40,705 --> 00:49:41,831
Stay right here.

517
00:49:41,915 --> 00:49:43,625
l'll wear him like underwear!

518
00:49:43,708 --> 00:49:44,792
Stay with me.

519
00:49:53,134 --> 00:49:56,221
Past the end are the gates to the square.

520
00:49:56,304 --> 00:49:57,305
Good.

521
00:50:05,146 --> 00:50:06,814
Reiben, where's the Captain from?

522
00:50:06,898 --> 00:50:09,651
Figure that out, you got yourself a prize.

523
00:50:09,734 --> 00:50:11,069
300 bucks, l heard.

524
00:50:11,152 --> 00:50:14,781
Company's got a pool. Five bucks gets you in.

525
00:50:18,159 --> 00:50:19,577
Easy.

526
00:50:21,162 --> 00:50:24,958
lt's around this corner. Defilade up to those gates.

527
00:50:26,751 --> 00:50:28,920
Somebody must know where he's from.

528
00:50:29,003 --> 00:50:32,423
Been with him since Kasserine Pass, and l don't know.

529
00:50:32,507 --> 00:50:34,050
My ankles are killing me.

530
00:50:34,133 --> 00:50:37,011
l'll need a wheelchair before this is over.

531
00:50:37,095 --> 00:50:39,639
Ow! That's it. Oh, my God.

532
00:50:39,722 --> 00:50:41,641
Got ankles like an old woman.

533
00:50:41,724 --> 00:50:43,017
Like an old...

534
00:50:46,145 --> 00:50:47,438
Reiben.

535
00:50:47,522 --> 00:50:49,649
So you don't even know where he went to school?

536
00:50:49,732 --> 00:50:51,651
Captain didn't go to school,

537
00:50:51,734 --> 00:50:54,571
they assembled him out of Gl body parts.

