Either Mr Mellish or Mr Jackson needs that.

1577
02:09:53,810 --> 02:09:54,894
Yes, sir.

1578
02:09:56,020 --> 02:09:57,397
Upham! Jackson's fine.

1579
02:09:57,480 --> 02:09:58,481
Turn around to Mellish.

1580
02:10:20,044 --> 02:10:23,673
l don't know if they took the bait, Captain.

1581
02:10:48,698 --> 02:10:51,075
You got any more of that?

1582
02:11:36,704 --> 02:11:38,665
Panzers didn't take the bait.

1583
02:11:43,753 --> 02:11:46,798
lnfantry's moving to the left.

1584
02:11:46,881 --> 02:11:50,260
Half-track just went by with about 20 troops.

1585
02:13:30,693 --> 02:13:32,904
Displace!

1586
02:13:53,883 --> 02:13:55,718
Do it now! Light it!

1587
02:13:55,802 --> 02:13:57,637
You! Light it!

1588
02:14:08,940 --> 02:14:10,984
30 infantry on the right flank!

1589
02:14:11,067 --> 02:14:13,653
Get over there and stop 'em!

1590
02:14:13,736 --> 02:14:14,904
Displace!

1591
02:14:26,791 --> 02:14:27,876
Upham!

1592
02:14:43,516 --> 02:14:44,684
Clear!

1593
02:14:46,936 --> 02:14:47,979
Krauts!

1594
02:14:49,981 --> 02:14:51,107
Right flank!

1595
02:15:03,536 --> 02:15:05,288
Sanitater!

1596
02:15:27,894 --> 02:15:30,939
Get down! Get down!

1597
02:15:37,278 --> 02:15:40,323
Upham! Upham! .30-cal! Hurry!

1598
02:15:40,406 --> 02:15:44,035
And find the captain! This flank's going to fold!

1599
02:16:38,798 --> 02:16:41,217
Reversing! He's still in this fight!

1600
02:16:42,802 --> 02:16:45,763
No, no, Ryan, get down! Get down!

1601
02:17:22,091 --> 02:17:24,135
- Ryan. - Get off me!

1602
02:17:24,219 --> 02:17:26,721
- You all right? - Get off me!

1603
02:17:26,805 --> 02:17:28,807
l'm fine, too, Captain(!)

1604
02:17:28,890 --> 02:17:31,476
OK, both sides!

1605
02:17:31,559 --> 02:17:33,520
Get a grenade in there!

1606
02:17:37,190 --> 02:17:38,608
Grenade!

1607
02:17:40,652 --> 02:17:43,571
- 20-mil! - 20-mil!

1608
02:17:43,655 --> 02:17:45,490
Flak gun. Take it out!

1609
02:17:58,878 --> 02:18:02,215
Heavy weapon below! l ain't got a shot!

1610
02:18:06,886 --> 02:18:08,721
Pincer move, Parker!

1611
02:18:08,805 --> 02:18:10,265
Targets eight o'clock low!

1612
02:18:10,348 --> 02:18:11,307
Shit!

1613
02:18:11,391 --> 02:18:12,934
God grant me strength.

1614
02:18:26,906 --> 02:18:28,867
Come on! Displace!

1615
02:18:28,950 --> 02:18:29,951
Come on!

1616
02:18:46,468 --> 02:18:48,052
Cover, Upham! Cover!

1617
02:18:48,136 --> 02:18:49,596
Cover!

1618
02:19:05,904 --> 02:19:08,072
l'm out of .30-calibre.

1619
02:19:10,658 --> 02:19:13,369
Blessed be the Lord, my strength,

1620
02:19:13,453 --> 02:19:15,788
which teaches my hands to war.

1621
02:19:24,756 --> 02:19:27,342
My goodness and my fortress...

1622
02:19:27,425 --> 02:19:29,636
my high tower and my deliverer...

1623
02:19:32,931 --> 02:19:35,725
my shield and He in whom l trust.

1624
02:20:03,837 --> 02:20:05,255
Parker, get down!

1625
02:20:27,277 --> 02:20:29,571
Captain, that 20-millimetre's killing us.

1626
02:20:29,654 --> 02:20:32,157
We gotta try to flank it.

1627
02:20:32,240 --> 02:20:35,827
Well, let me get over for the top shot.

1628
02:21:21,998 --> 02:21:24,709
Upham, ammo, Goddamit!

1629
02:22:07,168 --> 02:22:09,963
l'm jammed! l'm jammed! Got any .30-cal?

1630
02:22:10,046 --> 02:22:11,798
- l'm out. - Shit.

1631
02:23:52,148 --> 02:23:55,902
l'm out! l need a bandolier! Anybody got a bandolier?

1632
02:24:21,302 --> 02:24:24,889
God! God!

1633
02:24:27,767 --> 02:24:28,977
You stupid...

1634
02:25:14,439 --> 02:25:17,233
Let's stop. Listen to me! Listen to me! Stop!

1635
02:25:17,317 --> 02:25:19,694
No! D-d-d-d...Stop. Stop.

1636
02:25:55,021 --> 02:25:57,690
Son of...son of a bitch!

1637
02:25:57,774 --> 02:26:00,527
Son of a bitch! Son of a bitch!

1638
02:26:00,610 --> 02:26:02,111
Son of a bitch!

1639
02:26:03,196 --> 02:26:05,114
Son of a bitch!

1640
02:27:24,068 --> 02:27:25,445
l'm out.

1641
02:27:25,528 --> 02:27:26,946
Those .60 rounds.

1642
02:27:28,823 --> 02:27:30,200
We can use them without the tube.

1643
02:27:30,283 --> 02:27:31,784
How?

1644
02:27:31,868 --> 02:27:35,205
Fuse-arming wire, set back, heave it!

1645
02:27:50,136 --> 02:27:51,429
Panzer schreck!

1646
02:28:26,297 --> 02:28:28,341
We're going to the Alamo.

1647
02:28:38,351 --> 02:28:40,228
Alamo! Alamo!

1648
02:29:00,165 --> 02:29:02,208
We'll take it! You fall back!

1649
02:29:02,292 --> 02:29:03,793
You be right behind us!

1650
02:29:03,877 --> 02:29:05,879
Soon as we're in business!

1651
02:29:09,924 --> 02:29:11,176
Displace.

1652
02:29:14,512 --> 02:29:15,513
Reload.

1653
02:30:04,979 --> 02:30:06,564
All right, go.

1654
02:30:07,774 --> 02:30:10,568
We're blowing the bridge! Clear the bridge!

1655
02:30:34,634 --> 02:30:36,970
Sarge! Mike, are you all right?

1656
02:30:37,053 --> 02:30:41,015
- l just got the winded. - Get out of here!

1657
02:30:41,099 --> 02:30:43,184
We're gonna blow this bridge!

1658
02:30:45,270 --> 02:30:46,896
Come on, come on!

1659
02:30:51,568 --> 02:30:53,945
Tiger coming! Coming across the bridge!

1660
02:32:41,719 --> 02:32:42,720
Captain.

1661
02:32:46,432 --> 02:32:49,519
Captain, where are you going? Get back here!

1662
02:35:15,123 --> 02:35:16,958
Hang in there, Captain.

1663
02:36:02,170 --> 02:36:03,213
Medic!

1664
02:36:06,758 --> 02:36:07,842
Medic!

1665
02:36:07,926 --> 02:36:09,552
We got a medic?

1666
02:36:15,600 --> 02:36:18,353
They're tank-busters, sir. P-51s.

1667
02:36:19,604 --> 02:36:21,439
Angels on our shoulders.

1668
02:36:27,654 --> 02:36:28,780
What, sir?

1669
02:36:34,577 --> 02:36:38,581
James... Earn this.

1670
02:36:43,294 --> 02:36:45,004
Earn it.

1671
02:37:14,200 --> 02:37:17,537
My dear Mrs Ryan,

1672
02:37:17,620 --> 02:37:20,081
it's with a profound sense of joy

1673
02:37:20,165 --> 02:37:24,961
that l write to inform you your son Private James Ryan

1674
02:37:25,044 --> 02:37:27,547
is well and, at this very moment,

1675
02:37:27,630 --> 02:37:30,800
on his way home from European battlefields.

1676
02:37:30,884 --> 02:37:34,929
Reports from the front indicate James did his duty in combat

1677
02:37:35,013 --> 02:37:38,808
with great courage and steadfast dedication

1678
02:37:38,892 --> 02:37:41,561
even after informed of the tragic loss

1679
02:37:41,644 --> 02:37:45,482
your family has suffered in this great campaign

1680
02:37:45,565 --> 02:37:48,776
to rid the world of tyranny and oppression.

1681
02:37:48,860 --> 02:37:52,322
l take great pleasure in joining the Secretary of War,

1682
02:37:52,405 --> 02:37:54,240
the United States Army

1683
02:37:54,324 --> 02:37:56,951
and the citizens of a grateful nation

1684
02:37:57,035 --> 02:38:00,330
in wishing you good health and many years of happiness

1685
02:38:00,413 --> 02:38:03,416
with James at your side.

1686
02:38:03,500 --> 02:38:08,213
Nothing, not even the safe return of a beloved son,

1687
02:38:08,296 --> 02:38:12,759
can compensate you or the thousands of other families

1688
02:38:12,842 --> 02:38:16,262
who have suffered great loss in this tragic war.

1689
02:38:16,346 --> 02:38:19,098
l share with you some words which sustained me

1690
02:38:19,182 --> 02:38:23,520
through long, dark nights of peril, loss and heartache.

1691
02:38:23,603 --> 02:38:26,648
And l quote,

1692
02:38:26,731 --> 02:38:28,650
''l pray that our heavenly father

1693
02:38:28,733 --> 02:38:31,694
''may assuage the anguish of your bereavement

1694
02:38:31,778 --> 02:38:33,947
''and leave you only the cherished memory

1695
02:38:34,030 --> 02:38:35,865
''of the loved and lost

1696
02:38:35,949 --> 02:38:38,827
''and the solemn pride that must be yours

1697
02:38:38,910 --> 02:38:41,579
''to have laid so costly a sacrifice

1698
02:38:41,663 --> 02:38:43,998
''upon the alter of freedom.

1699
02:38:44,082 --> 02:38:46,126
''Abraham Lincoln.''

1700
02:38:46,209 --> 02:38:48,795
Yours very sincerely and respectfully,

1701
02:38:48,878 --> 02:38:51,756
George C Marshall, General, Chief of Staff.

1702
02:39:42,932 --> 02:39:46,102
My family is with me today.

1703
02:39:46,186 --> 02:39:48,480
They wanted to come with me.

1704
02:39:50,690 --> 02:39:52,275
To be honest with you,

1705
02:39:52,358 --> 02:39:56,112
l wasn't sure how l'd feel coming back here.

1706
02:39:58,490 --> 02:40:02,202
Every day l think about what you said to me

1707
02:40:02,285 --> 02:40:04,329
that day on the bridge.

1708
02:40:05,497 --> 02:40:10,668
And l've tried to live my life the best l could.

1709
02:40:10,752 --> 02:40:13,922
l hope that was enough.

1710
02:40:14,005 --> 02:40:17,091
l hope that, at least in your eyes,

1711
02:40:18,468 --> 02:40:22,305
l've earned what all of you have done for me.

1712
02:40:35,652 --> 02:40:36,945
James.

1713
02:40:39,239 --> 02:40:41,449
Captain John H Miller.

1714
02:40:49,916 --> 02:40:52,710
Tell me l've led a good life.

1715
02:40:52,794 --> 02:40:53,920
What?

1716
02:40:55,004 --> 02:40:57,465
Tell me l'm a good man.

1717
02:41:04,556 --> 02:41:06,182
You are.
